6.9 We recommended and the Management agreed that the Municipal
Accountant enhance the disclosure in the Notes to Financial Statements
particularly the Financial Liabilities to include additional information on
Loans Payable Account such as the following:
 The name of lending institutions;
 Purpose of the loan;
 The principal amounts;
 Terms of the loan; and
 Loan status as of December 31.

We recommended that the Management comply with the inventory accounting system/process including the forms to be used and the reports to be prepared as prescribed in the Government Accounting Manual for LGUs by observing following:

Perpetual Inventory System shall be used (Section 182 of the Manual);

The Accounting Unit and Supply Officer shall prepare and maintain the Supplies Ledger Card and Stock Cards, respectively. (Section 188 of GAM for LGUs, Volume I);

Inventory Custodian Slip (ICS) shall be issued for issuance of tangible items amounting to ₱15,000.00 or less and has a useful life of more than one year (Section 183 of GAM for LGUs, Volume I and Section 59 of GAM for LGUs, Volume I);

Requisition and Issue Slip (RIS) shall be prepared for every request of supplies and materials. Monthly RSMI shall be prepared and submitted to accounting unit for recording in the books; and

Inventories shall be recognized following the accounting entries prescribed under Section 192 of GAM for LGUs, Volume I.

